00:16:12,024 --> 00:16:13,892
I said, "How much money
do you need?"

241
00:16:13,893 --> 00:16:16,628
And they said,
"Two and a halfmillion dollars."

242
00:16:16,629 --> 00:16:19,629
And I said, "Okay."

243
00:16:19,799 --> 00:16:22,567
"What percentage
of the company do you think
you'd be happy giving up...

244
00:16:22,568 --> 00:16:25,568
for two and a half
million dollars?"

245
00:16:26,639 --> 00:16:29,639
And they thought and said,
"Well, how about half?"

246
00:16:30,209 --> 00:16:33,209
And I said, "That's fine."

247
00:16:34,413 --> 00:16:36,214
And within a day and a half,

248
00:16:36,215 --> 00:16:39,215
I had raised two and a half
million dollars.

249
00:16:46,459 --> 00:16:49,459
Intel opened its doors in July of'68,

250
00:16:49,795 --> 00:16:52,795
and Arthur Rock's partnership
with its founders
was only just beginning.

251
00:16:54,166 --> 00:16:57,166
Arthur was our chairman
of the board in those days.

252
00:16:57,937 --> 00:17:00,937
I spent a lot oftime there.

253
00:17:02,174 --> 00:17:05,174
Venture capitalists
do write the check,

254
00:17:05,578 --> 00:17:08,413
but that isn't all we do.

255
00:17:08,414 --> 00:17:11,414
Writing a check is easy.

256
00:17:11,851 --> 00:17:14,851
Yeah, it doesn't take much ink.

257
00:17:19,258 --> 00:17:21,126
I attended staffmeetings.

258
00:17:21,127 --> 00:17:22,861
Arthur asked good questions.

259
00:17:22,862 --> 00:17:24,896
I was on the phone to them a lot.

260
00:17:24,897 --> 00:17:26,965
Was an excellent board member.
Offer advice.

261
00:17:26,966 --> 00:17:29,000
Planning.
Setting up an audit committee.

262
00:17:29,001 --> 00:17:31,269
Customer relations.
Interviewed a lot ofpeople.

263
00:17:31,270 --> 00:17:33,805
Built all the pieces
ofan enterprise.

264
00:17:33,806 --> 00:17:36,806
I just brought what I consider
common sense to the table.

265
00:17:37,910 --> 00:17:40,910
He even met his wife there.

266
00:17:43,049 --> 00:17:46,049
He gave us guidance
on when not to go public
as well as when to go public.

267
00:17:49,088 --> 00:17:51,156
I was very involved in that.

268
00:17:51,157 --> 00:17:54,157
This was all new to Intel,
but wasn't new to me.

269
00:17:55,094 --> 00:17:58,094
We went public the same day
that Playboy Enterprises went public.

270
00:18:01,634 --> 00:18:03,668
At the same price.

271
00:18:03,669 --> 00:18:06,669
And a few years later
one of the analysts says,

