and exploit a new idea.

1133
01:17:55,290 --> 01:17:58,290
We would all have a lower
standard of living, worldwide.

1134
01:17:59,094 --> 01:18:02,030
It clearly got
the first man to the moon.

1135
01:18:02,031 --> 01:18:04,899
It clearly got, you know,

1136
01:18:04,900 --> 01:18:07,900
everything from
we're country code 1
in the telephone system to,

1137
01:18:09,004 --> 01:18:10,638
you know, the Internet.

1138
01:18:10,639 --> 01:18:13,639
I think you can't ignore
the role ofventure capital.

1139
01:18:16,445 --> 01:18:19,445
You know, can you imagine,
a guy going in and talking to a banker,

1140
01:18:19,448 --> 01:18:22,448
and he says, you know,
"Look, I want to start
delivering mail by jets."

1141
01:18:23,919 --> 01:18:26,919
We go into Kleiner Perkins,
we say we want to make
insulin in bacteria,

1142
01:18:27,690 --> 01:18:28,956
and he goes, "Okay!"

1143
01:18:28,957 --> 01:18:31,957
Great things don't really
come out of the status quo.

1144
01:18:33,162 --> 01:18:36,162
They come out of people
with vision and drive
to prove the difference.

1145
01:18:36,932 --> 01:18:39,932
This underlying technology
was there,

